We are using the 2025.2.1.0 of robotpy. After running robotpy sync and deploying, the code deploys successfully, but on the driver station console, we get: Fatal python error, unhandled exception instantiating MyRobot. And the driver station shows no robot code.
We tried reverting back to an older version before we updated the versions to 2025 and we got the same thing.
We tried reimaging the Roborio and updating the driver station with no luck. We have a roborio 1.
Any help is appreciated!

Hello! So we found the problem. We are having trouble with the updates for pathplanner 2025. We are trying to use AutoBuilder.configureHolomonic(
self.getPose,
self.resetOdometry
self.getChassisSpeeds,
lambda speeds, feedforwards: self.driveChassisSpeeds(speeds),
PPHolonomicDriveController(
PIDConstants(5.0, 0.0, 0.0),
PIDConstants(5.0, 0.0, 0.0)
),
config,
self.shouldFlipPath,
self )
But we are getting the error: AttributeError: type object ‘AutoBuilder’ has no attribute ‘configureHolonomic’
We looked at the 2025 pathplanner docs and they do it the same way and we double checked that the versions of pathplannerlib is correct.

The API documentation (Auto - pathplannerlib) and the class at pathplanner/pathplannerlib-python/pathplannerlib/auto.py at main · mjansen4857/pathplanner · GitHub does not seem to have a configureHolonomic method, so the documentation is wrong or there’s a bug in pathplanner.

I don’t maintain pathplanner, but I’ve filed a bug for you at Python documentation out of date? · Issue #1041 · mjansen4857/pathplanner · GitHub.

Help with the updates to pathplanner Python
Ok we found the solution. Just so no one else falls into the same hole as us, the pathplanner docs for Python is no updated for AutoBuilder.configureHolonomic. Refer to the docs as Python, but the Java version has all of the correct functions. To configure AutoBuilder, you can use the configure function instead.
